# Frontend Style Enforcement

Apply this rule before generating or editing frontend UI code.

## Pre-Generation Steps

1. Read `docs/styleguide/ui-styleguide.md`.
2. Reuse existing UI primitives before creating new component styles.
3. Keep accessibility behavior consistent (text scale, high contrast, mobile modal/menu interactions).

## Implementation Rules

- Prefer Tailwind utilities in component files.
- Use global CSS only for shared tokens/primitives in `client/src/index.css`.
- Keep interactions readable and predictable; avoid hidden/complex controls.
- For UI behavior changes, update relevant docs in `docs/styleguide/` in the same PR.
